        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure RHEL 9 to restrict exposed kernel pointer addresses access by adding the following line to a file in the "/etc/sysctl.d" directory:

kernel.kptr_restrict = 1

Remove any configurations that conflict with the above from the following locations: 
/run/sysctl.d/*.conf
/usr/local/lib/sysctl.d/*.conf
/usr/lib/sysctl.d/*.conf
/lib/sysctl.d/*.conf
/etc/sysctl.conf
/etc/sysctl.d/*.conf

The system configuration files need to be reloaded for the changes to take effect. To reload the contents of the files, run the following command:

$ sudo sysctl --system</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
