          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify the "/var/log" directory is group-owned by root with the following command:

$ stat -c "%G %n" /var/log

root /var/log

If "/var/log" does not have a group owner of "root", this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure the group owner of the directory "/var/log" to "root" by running the following command:

$ sudo chgrp root /var/log</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
