          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify RHEL 9 disables the graphical user interface autorun function with the following command:

Note: This requirement assumes the use of the RHEL 9 default graphical user interface, the GNOME desktop environment. If the system does not have any graphical user interface installed, this requirement is Not Applicable.

$ gsettings get org.gnome.desktop.media-handling autorun-never 

true

If "autorun-never" is set to "false", and is not documented with the information system security officer (ISSO) as an operational requirement, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure the GNOME desktop to disable the autorun function on removable media.

The dconf settings can be edited in the /etc/dconf/db/* location.

Update the [org/gnome/desktop/media-handling] section of the "/etc/dconf/db/local.d/00-security-settings" database file and add or update the following lines:

[org/gnome/desktop/media-handling]
autorun-never=true

Then update the dconf system databases:

$ sudo dconf update</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
