          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify RHEL 9 is configured to lock an account after three unsuccessful logon attempts with the command:

$ grep 'deny =' /etc/security/faillock.conf

deny = 3

If the "deny" option is not set to "3" or less (but not "0"), is missing or commented out, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
