        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Rule_Title</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>RHEL 9 must ensure account lockouts persist.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Vuln_Discuss</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Having lockouts persist across reboots ensures that account is only unlocked by an administrator. If the lockouts did not persist across reboots, an attacker could simply reboot the system to continue brute force attacks against the accounts on the system.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
