        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Check_Content</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify the "/etc/security/faillock.conf" file is configured to use a nondefault faillock directory to ensure contents persist after reboot with the following command:

$ sudo grep -w dir /etc/security/faillock.conf

dir = /var/log/faillock

If the "dir" option is not set to a nondefault documented tally log directory or is missing or commented out, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure RHEL 9 maintain the contents of the faillock directory after a reboot.

Add/modify the "/etc/security/faillock.conf" file to match the following line:

dir = /var/log/faillock</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
