          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>RHEL 9 must restrict the use of the "su" command.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Vuln_Discuss</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>The "su" program allows to run commands with a substitute user and group ID. It is commonly used to run commands as the root user. Limiting access to such commands is considered a good security practice.

Satisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
