          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>IA_Controls</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA />
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Check_Content</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify that RHEL 9 Audit Daemon is configured to label all offloaded audit logs, with the following command:

$ sudo grep name_format /etc/audit/auditd.conf

name_format = hostname

If the "name_format" option is not "hostname", "fqd", or "numeric", or the line is commented out, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Edit the /etc/audit/auditd.conf file and add or update the "name_format" option:

name_format = hostname

The audit daemon must be restarted for changes to take effect.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
