          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure RHEL 9 to generate audit records upon successful/unsuccessful attempts to use the "ssh-agent" command by adding or updating the following rule in "/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules":

-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/ssh-agent -F perm=x -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-ssh

To load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command:

$ sudo augenrules --load</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
