        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Check_Content</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify the audit system prevents unauthorized changes to logon UIDs with the following command:

$ sudo grep -i immutable /etc/audit/audit.rules

--loginuid-immutable

If the "--loginuid-immutable" option is not returned in the "/etc/audit/audit.rules", or the line is commented out, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure RHEL 9 auditing to prevent modification of login UIDs once they are set by adding the following line to /etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules:

--loginuid-immutable

The audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
